bal talent in operational roles. All Oceans talent comes from Sri Lanka.=C2=
=A0
Why Sri Lanka? Simple: it has the best talent-to-price ratio on the planet.=
 Oceans [ https://substack.com/redirect/6b8e2ba1-b22b-41c8-8eaf-c227170a8a6=
b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] recr=
uits, vets, trains, and employs top talent in the region from name brand fi=
rms and universities. You pay between $2,500 - $3,500 per month for a full =
time, embedded team member with 5-10 years of experience. That=E2=80=99s ~$=
36K/yr for talent that would cost $150K+ (easily) in the US.
They are already serving clients like Austin Reif (Morning Brew), Ndamukong=
 Suh (Philadelphia Eagles), Joe McCann (Asymmetric Financial) and dozens of=
 high growth SMBs. So if you=E2=80=99re looking for top, affordable talent =
to take on operational roles (EA+, Operations, Sales/Marketing, Finance, Ba=
ck Office), check out Oceans [ https://substack.com/redirect/6b8e2ba1-b22b-=
41c8-8eaf-c227170a8a6b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Monday! Hope you all had a great weekend.=20
I didn=E2=80=99t want to write about SVB. Everyone wrote about SVB. Some we=
re qualified to write about, some were making it up. What=E2=80=99s happeni=
ng in the banking sector is an important story, but it=E2=80=99s not one th=
at I can add much to.=20
Part of the SVB situation that caught me off guard though, and that is more=
 up Not Boring=E2=80=99s alley, is the strength of the anti-tech sentiment =
that=E2=80=99s emerged in its wake. That=E2=80=99s something I wanted to wr=
ite about. I=E2=80=99ve started about 15 drafts, trying to figure out what =
I wanted to say and how to say it. Here=E2=80=99s number 16.
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.=20
The Happiness Hypothesis
People don=E2=80=99t seem to like the tech industry as much as the tech ind=
ustry likes itself.=C2=A0
A small group is unhappy with technology generally, a larger one is unhappy=
 with the tech industry as it stands today, and an even larger one is unhap=
py with venture capitalists.=C2=A0
One Slate writer is particularly unhappy with VCs, opining on Twitter [ htt=
ps://substack.com/redirect/c39677a4-3bc7-488f-84e4-b135145898fe?j=3DeyJ1Ijo=
iOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], =E2=80=9CEuthani=
zing them is imperative if we want a better world.=E2=80=9D (Don=E2=80=99t =
worry, the euthanization thing was just a John Maynard Keynes reference [ h=
ttps://substack.com/redirect/44ece7df-6458-4a4c-bc33-6682c0414d25?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] lol!)=C2=A0
While the Slate writer=E2=80=99s opinion is intentionally extreme and incen=
diary, tens of thousands of people, from anonymous Twitter accounts to sitt=
ing Senators, have spent the past ten days expressing their distaste for te=
ch, tech bros, the tech industry, and VCs. Tech has become a punching bag f=
or the left, which paints it as too libertarian, and the right, which paint=
s it as too woke.=C2=A0
In response, people in tech have begun mounting defenses and offensives. Ev=
ery=E2=80=99s Evan Armstrong wrote a good piece arguing that Technology is =
Good Actually [ https://substack.com/redirect/89983087-8a53-474a-9fd4-42e5d=
9804de6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU =
]. Pirate Wire=E2=80=99s Mike Solana proposed [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/d9c00503-d183-40bc-8e4a-4a1a0436f4ca?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] industry collaboration and influence via =
political lobbying. Many, many tweeters have pointed out the irony of peopl=
e complaining about tech on (venture-backed) Twitter from their (venture-ba=
cked) iPhone. If you want to get into the nitty gritty of the back and fort=
h on whether VCs are evil and tech is bad, there are a lot of interesting r=
eads and listens out there.=C2=A0
To me, the much more interesting question is not who=E2=80=99s right or who=
