I=E2=80=99m not sure this is the essay I would have written a couple weeks =
ago. Over the past few weeks, though, in the comments section of our Weekly=
 Doses #30 [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4d7fb99-c53b-45ee-b604-266d70fd=
fe8b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] a=
nd #31 [ https://substack.com/redirect/b2705134-aa87-4111-8841-625c9e1b8159=
?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], a re=
ader named Ernest Prabhakar made some excellent points about Not Boring=E2=
=80=99s approach. Essentially, in nicer words, he pushed me to think about =
why not everyone is as techno-optimistic as I am instead of jamming my visi=
on of progress down their throats. In response to The AppetiZIRP [ https://=
substack.com/redirect/852fa7c1-522c-4695-8550-b5c157ae923a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], he made the challenge=
