s, especially at a time when things are changing so quickly and the stakes =
are so high.=C2=A0
If people who work in and invest in tech are definitionally the people who =
most believe that technology is good for humanity, it=E2=80=99s on us to wo=
rk constructively with politicians, and more importantly, to deliver produc=
ts so useful to average people that politicians can=E2=80=99t find an easy =
scapegoat in the tech industry.
That, of course, is easier said than done, because as we=E2=80=99ve covered=
, innovation isn=E2=80=99t a top-down thing but a bottoms-up, unpredictable=
, evolutionary one. I do think, however, that we=E2=80=99re at a really int=
eresting time when all of the past couple decades=E2=80=99 worth of iterati=
on has opened the door for products that will both improve peoples=E2=80=99=
