https://substack.com/redirect/489c43cb-8b5c-4c83-8212-9d37083d7167?j=3DeyJ1=
IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
The world=E2=80=99s knowledge isn=E2=80=99t just at our fingertips, but dir=
ectly piped into our brains, explorable and interpretable in a thought with=
 the assistance of AI nanobots.=C2=A0
Of course, in this future world, nobody has to work. All of the B2B softwar=
e created in the early 2000s served as a template for the workflow AIs, and=
 the workflow AIs took over from there. Plus, robots can deliver massages b=
etter than any human masseuse, haircuts finer than any human barber, and ho=
spitality more doting than any human concierge. Of course, they can take ou=
t the trash and build buildings and fight wars and make things on our behal=
f, too.=C2=A0
People are free to create with their hands or to explore imagined metaverse=
 worlds or sleep or read or ThinkTweet or run or to do, in Asimov=E2=80=99s=
 words, whatever they wish [ https://substack.com/redirect/8a46cc8a-9b53-4e=
70-9e7a-4db4456520cd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
Are people happier in this world?=C2=A0
That depends.=C2=A0
I tend to agree with Ernie=E2=80=99s observation that, =E2=80=9CThis is pre=
cisely why people are pessimistic in the face of increasing material progre=
ss. They=E2=80=99ve lost their old source of meaning from the struggle to s=
urvive, and can=E2=80=99t find their own way forward.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
As technology enables longer lives and more free time and more material abu=
ndance, it leaves an equal and opposite opportunity for humans to turn that=
 potential happiness into real happiness.=C2=A0
I won=E2=80=99t pretend to know the answer there =E2=80=94 there are probab=
ly as many answers as there are people =E2=80=94 but I=E2=80=99d love to he=
ar your thoughts.
