=2E Each company or person creates or ado=
pts each very specific technology fo=
r a very specific reason &#8211; there&#8217;s always a Job to Be Done &#82=
11; so the question is impractically grandiose. Pondering the ultimate purp=
ose of technology is like pondering the meaning of life.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">Maybe the AI can help. ChatGPT tells me that &#8220;Technology is a tool =
that is used to solve problems and make tasks easier and more efficient. It=
s purpose is to improve our daily lives and help us accomplish things that =
would be difficult or impossible to do without it.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But =
which problems? Which tasks? Which things? Improve our daily lives, how, ex=
actly? Why?</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If technology is a &#8220;bicycle for the mind,&#8=
221; or a lever that humans use to do the things we want to do more easily =
and efficiently, then determining what to do with technology is a matter of=
 asking what humanity&#8217;s goals are in the first place. Why are we here=
?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s a personal question, and maybe an unanswera=
ble one, but given the expected pace and type of technological progress in =
the coming years, it&#8217;s worth trying to come up with something that&#8=
217;s close enough to right to be actionable.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In </span>=
<em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/2a37432b-8cad-405b-80b9-b82f2f=
ff538d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" =
rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">The Purpose =
of Technology</a></em><span>, Balaji proposed an answer: &#8220;If the prox=
imate purpose of technology is to </span><strong>reduce scarcity</strong><s=
pan>, the ultimate purpose of technology is to </span><strong>eliminate mor=
tality</strong><span>.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We can go a level d=
eeper. Why do we want to reduce scarcity? Why do we want to eliminate morta=
lity? I think it all comes back to increasing the potential for human happi=
ness, moment-to-moment, day-to-day.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>Potential</em><span> i=
s the key word here. Even the Founding Fathers, while promising Life and Li=
berty themselves to be unalienable rights, could only grant the right to th=
e </span><em>Pursuit</em><span> of Happiness.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"c=
olor: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><sp=
an>Reducing scarcity and eliminating mortality increase the </span><em>pote=
ntial</em><span> for human happiness. Living longer, healthier lives means =
more time to enjoy life. Reducing suffering and loss means less time suffer=
ing and grieving. But smaller things &#8211; the ability to reconnect with =
old friends, make more money in fewer hours, learn about things that fascin=
ate you, experience the wonder of </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/re=
direct/859ddfb9-6d56-4f18-91fc-eb6888007fc4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text=
-decoration: underline;">magical technology</a><span> &#8211; increase the =
potential for human happiness, too.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404=
040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Just ho=
w good a certain technology might be at serving its purpose can be gauged b=
ased on its ability to increase the potential for human happiness. Happines=
s is, of course, a hard thing to pin down. The </span><em><a href=3D"https:=
//substack.com/redirect/ffdaf5f5-599a-4d33-b005-ecc3a5c1f186?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"col=
or: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">World Happiness Report</a></em><s=
pan> uses six factors &#8211; levels of GDP, life expectancy, generosity, s=
ocial support, freedom, and corruption &#8211; to rank countries by Happine=
ss, but it&#8217;s necessarily imprecise.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color=
: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>B=
